President Obama spoke with President Alvaro Colom of Guatemala to express his regret about the sexually transmitted disease inoculation study conducted by the U.S. Public Health Service in the 1940s. He apologized to all those affected and reaffirmed the United States' commitment to conducting medical studies that meet legal and ethical standards. The President also emphasized the importance of the bilateral relationship between the United States and Guatemala. A photograph of the President during the call is available.